headlines.description: — Joel Embiid won one for the 76ers in 60 seconds.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid returns from injury, powers 76ers past Hawks 104-101

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis scored a career-high 41 points, including 29 in the first half, and the Washington Wizards beat Minnesota 142-127 on Monday night after Timberwolves star Karl-Anthony-Towns was helped off the court in the third quarter with a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis scores 41, Wizards beat Wolves after Towns hurt

headlines.description: — The reigning NBA Defensive Player of the Year showed he can do it on offense, too.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smart dishes 15, scores 22, Celtics crush Hornets 140-105

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored a season-high 45 points, carrying the Brooklyn Nets to a 109-102 victory over the Orlando Magic on Monday night that got them back to .500.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 45, carries Nets to 109-102 win over Magic

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 18 points and 11 rebounds in his return from injury, O.G. Anunoby scored 20 and the Toronto Raptors beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 100-88 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 18 in return, Raptors beat Cavaliers 100-88

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 23 points, matched his career high with eight assists and converted a go-ahead three-point play with 44 seconds left to lift the short-handed New Orleans Pelicans to a 105-101 victory over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Monday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson powers short-handed Pelicans past Thunder 105-101

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 32 points and 12 rebounds, Jamal Murray scored a season-high 31 and the Denver Nuggets defeated the Houston Rockets 129-113 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Murray lead Nuggets to 129-113 win over Rockets

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan had 26 points and six assists to lead the Chicago Bulls to a 114-107 victory over the Utah Jazz on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan scores 26, Bulls hand Jazz fifth straight loss

headlines.description: — Devin Booker had 44 points, eight rebounds and six steals, and the Phoenix Suns extended their winning streak to five with a 122-117 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 44, Suns top Kings 122-117 for 5th straight

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Rookie Andrew Nembhard hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer, and the Indiana Pacers rallied from a 17-point deficit in the fourth quarter for a stunning 116-115 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rookie Nembhard hits 3 at buzzer, Pacers stun Lakers 116-115
